    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted because the COU is explicitly scoped to the ASTM F1717 standard configuration and no regulatory requirement for multi-condition testing applies to this submission. All quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval <1.96, relative difference <10%) are satisfied for all three QoIs. The FEA ensemble is judged sufficiently credible to support the regulatory decision for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw under compression-bending.",
